In the LookAndFeel dialog there are 2 file-input fields for _Logo_ and _Favicon_. These fields will prevent the rest of the page to load/render successfully, if the following is the case:

An add-on is active, which has a {{web-resource}} module with context set to {{atl.admin}} and a dependency to {{jira-fields}} (other dependencies may also cause the problem).

The dependency to {{jira-fields}} will include the content of _initInlineAttach.js_ to the page, which in turn will search for all file-input fields ({{input\[type=file\]}}) and handle them in a special way. The problem is that some extra html content is expected, which is not present for the _Logo_ and _Favicon_ fields. Therefore the javascript will fail with the following exception:
{code}Unable to find maximum upload size on form.{code}

*Suggestion:*
That can be prevented if the file-input fields for _Logo_ and _Favicon_ have the class {{ignore-inline-attach}} (see [this Answers thread|https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/134862/file-upload-in-custom-plugin?page=1#134912]). The plugin _Jira Admin Helper_ [apparently once triggered that problem|https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/90321/look-and-feel-editor-fails-after-install-of-jira-admin-helper-plugin].
Btw. JIRA already uses the class {{ignore-inline-attach}} in the avatar picker when selecting a new avatar in your own profile.

