Recently JIRA has begun to use the more intuitive term of 'Export' to refer to operations involving exporting JIRA data or search results to other formats, instead of the classical way this was referenced in older versions 'Views'. These changes have been made all over the UI, menus and documentation, which is excellent

However, configuration parameters or keys in many places still use the classic JIRA 'Views' terminology making it a bit un-intuitive or confusing to new JIRA Admins trying to perform some advanced configuration

Some examples to illustrate the point:
* {{jira.search.views.default.max}} could be {{jira.search.export.default.max}}
* {{jira.search.views.max.unlimited.group}} could be {{jira.search.export.max.unlimited.group}}
* {{jira.search.views.max.limit}} could be {{jira.search.export.max.limit}}
* also {{jira.search.views.default.max}} could be {{jira.search.export.default.max}}
etc.
